This paper focuses on the human-robot interface for UAV path planning, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the use of virtual reality (VR) for this purpose, which is a subfield of computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves the use of UAVs, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and safety of the interface, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
